Below is the step-by-step checklist to run QueryMind locally.

1) Prerequisites
Python 3.10+
A PostgreSQL database you can connect to (Neon/Supabase/local)
A Groq API key (needed for the NL→SQL agent endpoint)
2) Create a DB user (read-only recommended)
In your Postgres, create a user that can only read (example):

CREATE USER querymind_ro WITH PASSWORD 'strong_password';
GRANT CONNECT ON DATABASE your_db TO querymind_ro;
GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA public TO querymind_ro;
GRANT SELECT ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO querymind_ro;
ALTER DEFAULT PRIVILEGES IN SCHEMA public GRANT SELECT ON TABLES TO querymind_ro;
Use that user in your DATABASE_URL.

3) Setup the project (Windows PowerShell)
From the project root:

cd D:\Atharva_Projects\QueryMind
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
copy .env.example .env
4) Fill in .env (this is what you “need to give”)
Edit .env and set at least:

DATABASE_URL (required)

Format: postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DBNAME
Neon/Supabase will give you host/port/db/user/password.
GROQ_API_KEY (required for /api/v1/agent/query)

Optional but useful:

MAX_QUERY_ROWS=500
STATEMENT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=30
AGENT_MAX_RETRIES=3
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
LOG_AGENT_SQL=true
Keep ALLOW_ADHOC_SQL=false (safer)
5) Run the FastAPI backend
uvicorn backend.main:create_app --factory --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
Check:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/health
http://127.0.0.1:8000/ready
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
6) Run the Streamlit UI (recommended)
Open a new PowerShell (same venv activated), then:

cd D:\Atharva_Projects\QueryMind
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
streamlit run frontend/app.py
In the sidebar, keep API base URL as http://127.0.0.1:8000.

7) (Optional) Run the MCP server standalone
You do not need to run this manually for the agent (the API spawns it), but for testing MCP tools with an MCP client:

python -m mcp_server.server
8) Quick test query
In Streamlit, ask something like:

“Show current database and server time”
Or a real question that matches your tables
Or via API docs: POST /api/v1/agent/query with:

{"question":"List 5 rows from public.your_table","max_rows":5}
If you paste (1) your DB provider (Neon/Supabase/local) and (2) a sample table name you have, I’ll give you the exact first question to try that will work with your schema.